  "time_ut": 1656855805,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0daf\u0dd9\u0db4\u0dcf \u0d85\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dd2 \u0db8\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0db6\u0dd9\u0dc4\u0dd9\u0dad\u0dca \u0d9c\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0dc4\u0dd2\u0da7\u0db4\u0dd4 \u0dbb\u0dab\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0da7 \u0dad\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dca \u0daf\u0dd3 \u00a0\u0db1\u0dd1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The former war hero was not given oil to take medicine for his mother who lost her legs",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A sad news is reported from Suriyawewa area that a soldier who was disabled by a bomb during the war while serving in the navy was not given fuel to take his legless mother to Karapitiya Hospital.",
        "The ex-naval disabled soldier said that when he went to the IOC petrol station and asked for fuel with a letter from the Suriyawewa Divisional Secretary, he refused to provide fuel.",
        "A 39-year-old KR Priyantha, a resident of Mbahu Suriyawewa, Valsapugala area, who served in the Navy, was disabled in 2006 due to a Tiger Claymo bomb attack and left the service.",
        "I was shot for the country. Today, both my mother's wings are cut, so there is no way I can take her to the Karapitiya hospital. I took a letter from the Suriyawewa Divisional Secretary and went to the shed with my mother's medical records. Suriyawewa also told Mr. O.I.C. He also told an army officer who was there. No one cared. They said they can't give that much oil.",
        "I feel that there is no meaning today that we risked our lives to serve the country. He said, \"Remember that this is how the gentlemen of the army are also treated when they retire.\""
      ],
